  "parent": "sla",
  "notes": "Standard Moscow Russian. Key features: pervasive palatalisation contrast, Аканье (unstressed /o/ → [ɐ]), г = [ɡ] plosive, final obstruent devoicing. FINAL DEVOICING: all obstruents devoiced in coda/word-final position (б→п, в→ф, г→к, д→т, з→с, ж→ш). VOWEL REDUCTION: о/а reduce to [ɐ] in 1st pretonic syllable, [ə] elsewhere (unstressed). IOTATED VOWELS: е/я/ю/ё preceded by [j] word-initially and after vowels. Г IN GENITIVE: -ого/-его endings: г→[v] (его=[jɪvo]). Sources: Avanesov (1956), Jones & Ward (1969), Padgett (2002).",
